Class DJIGroundStationExecutionPushInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • dji.sdk.api.GroundStation.DJIGroundStationExecutionPushInfo

  • public class DJIGroundStationExecutionPushInfo
extends java.lang.Object

    DJI Ground Station Execution Push Info Class

    While the aircraft is executing a ground station waypoint mission, information about the status of the mission can be found in this structure. This structure is used in the DJIGroundStationExecutionPushInfoCallback interface, which is called when the mobile device receives information pushed from the aircraft.
    Developers can use this class with DJIGroundStationExecutionPushInfoCallback to monitor and notify users of the current state of the waypoint mission execution.
    Version:
    V2.4.0
    Author:
    DJI Software
    See Also:
    DJIGroundStation, DJIGroundStationWaypoint

    • Field Detail

      • eventType

        public DJIGroundStationTypeDef.GroundStationExecutionPushType eventType
        This enum is used to keep track of the general stage of the mission execution the aircraft is in.
        Navi_Upload_Finish - The mission has just finished uploading to the aircraft.
        Navi_Mission_WayPoint_Reach_Point - The aircraft has just reached a waypoint.
        Navi_Mission_Finish - The aircraft has just finished its waypoint mission.
        See Also:
        DJIGroundStation, DJIGroundStationWaypoint

      • isMissionValid

        public boolean isMissionValid
        Indicates whether the uploaded mission is valid or not. Missions have limitations that must be adhered to. f you attempt to upload a mission that breaks these limitations using uploadGroundStationTask (in DJIGroundStation), he callback will return a GroundStationResult enum identifying why the mission is invalid.
        See Also:
        DJIGroundStation, DJIGroundStationWaypoint

      • estimateRunTime

        public int estimateRunTime
        The estimated amount of time, in seconds, that the entire waypoint mission will take to complete. Please note that if you influence the aircraft's speed during its mission using the remote controller, then estimateRunTime will no longer be accurate.
        See Also:
        DJIGroundStation, DJIGroundStationWaypoint

      • isRepeat

        public int isRepeat
        Used to monitor the status of the aircraft when it is executing a waypoint mission that is set to repeat.
        0 - NULL. Occurs when pauseGroundStationTask has been called (in DJIGroundStation).
        1 - FINISH. The aircraft has completed all of its repititions of the waypoint mission.
        2 - RESTART. The aircraft is the process of restarting the waypoint mission, meaning it is travelling from the final waypoint to the starting waypoint.
        3 - GO HOME. The aircraft is returning home. This occurs at the end of the waypoint mission if go home has been set as the waypoint mission finishing action.
        4 - LAND. The aircraft is landing. This occurs at the end of the waypoint mission if land has been set as the waypoint mission finishing action.
        5 - TIME OUT GO HOME. The waypoint mission has timed out and the aircraft is returning home.
        See Also:
        DJIGroundStation, DJIGroundStationWaypoint

      • reserved

        public int reserved
        This attribute is used for internal purposes. Please ignore, do not modify.

      • wayPointIndex

        public int wayPointIndex
        The index of the current waypoint the aircraft is at. If the aircraft is travelling between waypoints, this value will be the index of the waypoint it is travelling away from.
        See Also:
        DJIGroundStation, DJIGroundStationWaypoint

      • currentState

        public int currentState
        To be used when executing a waypoint mission. Identifies what the aircraft is currently doing. There are 6 possible values:
        0 - Initializing waypoint mission
        1 - Moving between waypoints
        2 - Rotating at a waypoint
        3 - Executing an action at a waypoint
        4 - Has reached a waypoint and will shortly be performing actions
        5 - At a waypoint, and has finished executing actions at that waypoint
        See Also:
        DJIGroundStation, DJIGroundStationWaypoint
